# React Frontend Conventions

## Imports
- Always use `@alias` paths: `@pages/`, `@features/`, `@components/`, `@hooks/`, `@utils/`, `@core/`, `@/types/`
- NEVER use `@types/` (conflicts with npm @types namespace). Use `@/types/` instead.
- Never use relative paths that cross folder boundaries (e.g., no `../../hooks/`).

## Architecture
- **@pages/**: One component per route. Thin orchestration — compose feature components, never contain business logic.
- **@features/**: Feature-specific components. Self-contained per feature (auth, workspaces, projects, tasks).
- **@hooks/**: TanStack Query wrappers for server state. One file per backend resource.
- **@core/api/**: Axios instance with JWT interceptor. API functions grouped by resource.
- **@core/providers/**: App-level providers (QueryClient, Theme, Auth).

## Patterns
- Functional components only. No class components.
- No `any` type — use `unknown` and narrow, or define proper interfaces in `@types/`.
- Use TanStack Query for all server state. Use Zustand only for client-only state (auth token/user).
- Optimistic updates for task status changes (drag-and-drop).
- Always handle loading, error, and empty states — no blank screens.

## Styling
- Tailwind CSS utility classes. Use `cn()` helper from `@utils/cn` for conditional classes.
- shadcn/ui for base components. Customize via Tailwind, not inline styles.
